  "title": "Circular motion - tangential acceleration",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div>\n<include href=\"../Passage/VR616134.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><p class=\"passage_para\">Students experiment with a small marble sliding down a ramp into a vertical circular track of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. The friction between the marble and the surface is negligible.</p></div></div></div>\n</div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The magnitude of the tangential acceleration of the marble is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub tangential\"><math alttext=\"a sub tangential\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>tan</mtext></msub></math></span></span>. Which of the following statements correctly compares <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub tangential\"><math alttext=\"a sub tangential\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>tan</mtext></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"g\"><math alttext=\"g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>g</mi></math></span></span> when the marble has traveled beyond Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> but has not reached Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>, and provides a reason to support this claim?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i3",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub tangential is greater than g\"><math alttext=\"a sub tangential is greater than g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>tan</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>g</mi></math></span></span>, because the tangential acceleration is caused by a component of the gravitational force.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub tangential is greater than g\"><math alttext=\"a sub tangential is greater than g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>tan</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>g</mi></math></span></span>, because the tangential acceleration is caused by non-zero components of the gravitational and normal forces.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub tangential is less than g\"><math alttext=\"a sub tangential is less than g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>tan</mtext></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>g</mi></math></span></span>, because the tangential acceleration is caused by a component of the gravitational force.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub tangential is less than g\"><math alttext=\"a sub tangential is less than g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mtext>tan</mtext></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>g</mi></math></span></span>, because the tangential acceleration is caused by non-zero components of the gravitational and normal forces.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
